<!--
	All the values in the VF page are reffered using formule expression
	{! expression}
	What ever the value generated by the expression that is displayed in the page.
	{! 10} --- 10 
	{! 'sam'} --- sam

	1. How to pass data in the url <br/>
		a. single parameters 
		https://ap5.salesforce.com/apex/pageName?param=value
		Example : https://ap5.salesforce.com/apex/myPage?name=satish

	 	2. If you want to pass multiple parameters 
		Example : https://ap5.salesforce.com/apex/myPage?name=satish&phone=123

	2. Read the values form the url 
	   {!$Currrentpage.parameters.parametername}
		
	   {!$Currrentpage.parameters.name} 
	   {!$Currrentpage.parameters.age} 
	   {!$Currerntpage.parameters.salary}
	

	3. How to the read the data from Sobject .
	   a. Sobject : It is salesforce object.it will reffer to any one the standardObject or customobject.
	   b. If you want to reffer to any of the sobject ,we have to define sobject as standardController
			Example : StandardController ="Account" 
					  StandardController="Customer__c"
		c. If you want to reffer to the fields of a sobject then we need 
			  {! SobjectName.FieldName}
			  {! Account.Name} 
			  {! Contact.LastName}
			  {! Customer__c.Name}
			  {! Customer__c.Phone__c}
			  {! Account.Email__c}

	4. Reffering to the global data on the VF page 

		 {! $SobjectName.FieldName}
		 {! $Organization.Name} 
		 {! $user.LastName}
		 {! $User.FirstName}
			
	
		
-->

<apex:page standardController="Account">
    Expression <br/><br/>
    {!10} <br/>
    {!'sam'} <br/>
    {! 'sam'+'kiran'} <br/>
    {! 10+20 } <br/>
    <br/><br/>
    Data from URL : <br/>
    Name : {! $Currentpage.parameters.name} <br/>
    Phone:{! $Currentpage.parameters.age} <br/><br/>
    
    Sobject Data  <br/><br/>
    Account Name  :{! Account.Name} <br/>
    Account Phone :{! Account.Phone} <br/>
    Account Rating:{! Account.Rating}<br/><br/>
    
    Global Data  <br/>
    User LastName :{! $User.LastName} <br/>
    User FirstName:{! $User.FirstName} <br/>
    Organization  :{! $Organization.Name} <br/>
	    
</apex:page>